Shareholders of Portland Paints and Products Nigeria PLC, a subsidiary of UAC Nigeria PLC, has approved  a dividend of N39.67 million representing 5kobo for every 50kobo ordinary shares to shareholders on the register of members at close of business on May 6  to 10, 2019. Speaking at the company’s Annual General Meeting (AGM) held on May 30, 2019, at the Golden Tulip, Festac, Lagos, the Chairman of the company, Mrs. Esosa Balogun, said, “Despite the ongoing challenges within the economy, your company recorded a turnover of N2.83bn as at 31 December 2018 which represents an increase of 22 per cent over 2017 and a proﬁt after tax of N207m. We hope to sustain this trend and further improve on the performance of the company in 2019.” On the outlook for 2019, the chairman emphasised that the company would consolidate and build on the gains achieved in 2018, especially in the execution of the route-to-market strategy, as well as new business development initiatives. The chairman also announced changes on the board of the company. Mr. Larry Ettah resigned from the board eﬀective July 20, 2018.  Mr. Abdul Bello resigned from the board effective December 31, 2018. Mr. Mukhtar Yakasai also resigned eﬀective January 31, 2019. Mrs. Esosa Balogun was appointed to the board as a non-executive director. UAC maintains performance, profit hits N15bn Dangote enriches shareholders with N76.24bn GSK moves to resolve N1.5bn unclaimed dividend Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin